ith a unique serverId, bitronix.tm.disableJmx=true, and bitronix.tm.journal=null, then shut Bitronix down and clear the property after the test.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"ehcache-core also contains optional servlet, Hibernate, Terracotta, and replication integration classes; do not add those dependencies unless tests intentionally cover those integrations.\",\n    \"If update checks are not disabled, CacheManager startup may attempt outbound update-check behavior and leave timer activity, making tests less deterministic.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0bf9642168af9da8016a428ca6399081969cd93c175e6cd50f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1619, "output": 640, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29907, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782746269934, "responseId": "resp_0bf9642168af9da8016a428c9e6cd881969eb4d86b624295e2"}, "toolResults": []}
